The paper proposes a method for no-reference image quality assessment using machine learning techniques. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also uses a Siamese Network and fine-tuning, which are common techniques in multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of synthetic data, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
